      "content": "hey im studying for my ling class and im kinda stuck on this. i have two different paragraphs from people describing their research, and i need to figure out which one sounds more \"competent\" and \"intelligent\" for a formal academic paper. \n\ntext A: the study's primary objective was to analyze the correlation between socio-economic variables and educational outcomes in urban environments. we utilized a longitudinal approach to ensure data integrity.\n\ntext B: we been lookin at how where folks live and how much money they got affects how they do in school. we watched how things changed over a long time so we could be sure the data was right.\n\nwhich one makes the author look more like a serious scholar?",
